<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1898-02-17T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1898-02-17T00:00:00-05:00" n="1077" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1077">
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Count <persName type="from">Vinci</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Sherman</persName>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Translation.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Embassy
                                        of His Majesty the King of Italy.</hi><lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1898-02-17"><hi rend="italic">February 17,
                                    1898</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Mr. Secretary of State</hi>: His excellency the
                            minister for foreign affairs, by a telegram which reached me this
                            evening, has instructed me to convey to the United States Government an
                            expression of deep horror and heartfelt sympathy on account of the
                            terrible catastrophe that has befallen the <hi rend="italic">Maine.</hi></p>
                        <p>I have the honor to be the interpreter near Your Excellency of these
                            sentiments of my Government, and I avail myself, etc.,</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">G. C. Vinci.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>